# API Conventions

**Follow existing project conventions exactly.** Before writing new code, read nearby modules that solve a similar problem and mirror how they do it.

Workspace under `crates/`: **`mc-tracker`** binary (axum HTTP + background tasks) plus library crates. See `docs/rust-migration-plan.md` for architecture.

## Layout

| Area | Location |
|------|----------|
| Entry | `mc-tracker/src/main.rs` — config, pool, bootstrap admin, spawn manager, bind server |
| HTTP routes | `mc-tracker/src/api.rs` — public routes; `admin.rs`, `auth/` for nested routers |
| Auth | `mc-tracker/src/auth/` — session cookies, login rate limit, `require_admin` middleware |
| Server orchestration | `mc-tracker/src/manager.rs` — ping loop, VM push, timeseries queries |
| Shared DTOs | `mc-api-types/src/` — `request/` + `response/` modules |
| Postgres | `mc-db/src/db/` — pool, migrations, `schema`, `repos/*` |
| Models / settings | `mc-db/src/model/` — `AppSettings`, server rows |
| Ping | `mc-ping/src/java/`, `mc-ping/src/bedrock/` |
| Geo | `mc-geo/src/` — MaxMind download, cache, lookup |
| Metrics / insights | `mc-insights/src/metric/`, `mc-insights/src/core/` |
| Migrations | `mc-db/src/db/migrations/` — never edit applied migrations |

## Package boundaries

**One purpose per crate.** Do not mix DB access with domain logic in repos.

| Crate | Owns | Must not |
|-------|------|----------|
| `mc-db` | Pool, migrations, schema, models, `repos/*` CRUD/SQL | HTTP types, ping logic, PromQL |
| `mc-api-types` | Serde DTOs for API JSON | Business logic, DB access |
| `mc-ping` | Java/Bedrock protocol, DNS resolve, retry | HTTP, metrics push |
| `mc-geo` | ASN lookup, MMDB cache | HTTP handlers |
| `mc-insights` | VM push, PromQL, chart timeseries (`Insights`), chat summaries (`InsightsChat`) | Server config CRUD |
| `mc-tracker` | Routes, auth, ServerManager orchestration | Raw SQL (delegate to `mc-db`) |

**Call chain:** `api.rs` / `admin.rs` / `auth/handlers` → `ServerManager` or `mc-db::repos` → `mc-ping` / `mc-geo` / `mc-insights`.

**`mc-db/repos` rules:**
- Functions take primitive params (`DateTime`, `Uuid`, row structs) — not HTTP DTOs.
- No imports from `mc-tracker` or handler modules.
- Upsert/find/delete SQL only; orchestration lives in `manager.rs` or handlers.

## HTTP surface

- `GET /health` — public
- `GET /servers`, `GET /servers/{id}/timeseries` — public (dashboard)
- `/auth/*` — login, logout, me, signup (as implemented)
- `/admin/*` — require admin session (`require_admin` middleware)
- Handlers return JSON via `mc-api-types` DTOs; errors use `ErrorResponse`

## Auth

- HMAC-signed session cookies (`SESSION_SECRET` env). Login rate-limited.
- Bootstrap admin from `MC_TRACKER_ADMIN_USERNAME` / `MC_TRACKER_ADMIN_PASSWORD` when users table is empty.
- Never log passwords, session secrets, or VM auth tokens.

## Data storage split

**VictoriaMetrics** — time-series: per-server player counts (push on schedule; query via PromQL).

**PostgreSQL** — relational: `servers`, `users`, `app_settings`. Servers loaded into memory on startup; admin CRUD updates DB then refreshes manager.

## Background tasks (`manager.rs`)

1. Ping all tracked servers on interval (from `AppSettings`).
2. Push player-count samples to VictoriaMetrics.
3. Refresh DNS resolver / geo lookups as needed.

Use `tokio::time::interval` with `MissedTickBehavior::Skip`. Respect shutdown via cancellation / `select!`.

## Integration

- **New routes** — add handler + register in `router()`; keep handlers thin; DTOs in `mc-api-types`.
- **New PG tables** — new diesel migration + model + repo module.
- **New metrics** — extend `mc-insights` metric schema + push path + query builder; wire through `Insights` / `ServerManager`.
- **New ping behavior** — change `mc-ping` only; manager calls the public ping API.

## Surrounding context

Trace an existing route end-to-end (router → handler → manager/repo → mc-ping/mc-insights) before adding a sibling. No business logic in repos — delegate to `ServerManager` or service functions.
